headline: FedEx Expansion Projects Set Against Strong Share Momentum And Valuation Metrics
summary: FedEx announced a 1.6 million sq ft automated sort center in Memphis as part of a wide expansion project. The company is increasing its use of sustainable aviation fuel across its air network. FedEx is rolling out AI powered post purchase tracking and returns tools for customers and merchants. FedEx, listed on the NYSE under ticker NYSE:FDX, is pairing these projects with a recent share price of $362.54. headline: Longstanding AIM Mail Center Franchisee Renews Commitment to Serving Lake Wylie, South Carolina and Names Daughter as Co-Owner
summary: Annex Brands, Inc., a leading franchisor in the packing, shipping, and office services industries, is proud to announce the renewal of a franchise agreement for the AIM Mail Center location in Lake Wylie, South Carolina. This renewal reflects the ongoing dedication of Richard Winter with the addition of his daughter, Ashli Ornoski, to the business. Now that she is incorporated into the family business, they can continue providing essential shipping and office services to the local community.
